		<h1>How to define the Inline endpoint in ESB Graphical Editor</h1>
		<p>

			<strong>Complete the following procedure to add an inline endpoint to a proxy service in your ESB config project.</strong>
</p>

<p>
<ol>
<li>In proxy service design view, drag a endpoint (e.g. address endpoint) icon from the tool palette to the canvas.
</li>
<li>Double click the EndPoint figure to open its Properties view.</li>
<li>In  Properties view, under &#39;Basic&#39; category, set &#39;In Line&#39;  property to &#39;true&#39; (see below)</li>
</ol>
</p>
<p>
<br/><img src="images/Inline_endpoint_00.png" /><br/>
</p>
<br/>
<p>

<p>Above procedure also can apply to
</p>

<p><ul>
<li>Default EndPoints</li>
<li>Address EndPoints</li>
<li>Failover EndPoints</li>
<li>WSDL EndPoints</li>
<li>Load-Balance EndPoints</li>
<li>Named EndPoint</li>
<li>Recipient-List EndPoints</li>
</ul></p>


</p>
